## VM arguments for Telecom OTP application

## Name of the node
-name telecom@127.0.0.1

## Cookie for distributed erlang
-setcookie telecom_cookie_change_in_production

## Heartbeat management; auto-restarts VM if it dies or becomes unresponsive
-heart

## Enable kernel poll for better performance
+K true

## Async thread pool size (default: 64)
+A 128

## Increase ETS table limit (default: 1400)
+e 100000

## Set distribution buffer busy limit (default: 1024KB)
+zdbbl 32768

## Set maximum number of ports (default: 65536)
-env ERL_MAX_PORTS 100000

## Set maximum number of processes (default: 262144)
+P 1000000

## Scheduler settings
## Use all available CPU cores
+sbt db

## Enable SMP support
-smp enable

## Scheduler bind type
+sbt db

## Dirty scheduler settings (for CPU-intensive work)
+SDcpu 8:8

## Memory allocator tuning for high-throughput
+MBas aobf
+MBe true
+MBmmbcs 512
+MBsbct 2048

## Crash dump settings
-env ERL_CRASH_DUMP log/erl_crash.dump

## Enable time correction
+c true

## Kernel logger
-kernel logger_level info
